{"key":"processedPost-10705050","value":{"id":10705050,"first":10704658,"last":10714353,"when":1248044211,"utime":"07/20/09 01:56 AM","content":"If you do the initial rinse in HOT tap water, the grains are semi-pasteurized and can't sprout during the soak.&nbsp; 4 to 24 hours is fine, but over 24 and your success rate will drop because too many of the bacterial endospores will germinate and form new endospores by then.&nbsp; If you don't soak long enough, you risk popping the grains during the boil.&nbsp; The key is to soak just long enough so you soften the kernels and get no burst grains when you boil.<br />RR","title":"Re: Want as many Opinions on Soaking and Simmering Rye as possible.","forum":"Mushroom Cultivation"}}